## Plan

**Approach:** Implement the capture/storage layer for retros as a first-class artifact (design: docs/plans/product/etude-retro-command.md, Storage decision B + Phase B). Three pieces, modelled on the EVAL precedent (which reuses runmanifest types but owns its own refs/etude/evals/* namespace + writer), NOT on runmanifest.Writer (hardcodes refs/etude/runs). (1) extend the refstore namespace allowlist to permit refs/etude/retros/*; (2) add a new internal/retro package with a Writer (refstore.WriteCommit to refs/etude/retros/<id>), RetroIDBase + AllocateRetroId (copy eval.EvalIDBase/AllocateEvalID), reusing the runmanifest.Manifest TYPE + artifactstore as the on-disk schema; (3) add an `etude retro` parent command with a `capture` subcommand that stores an externally-authored retro body, recording cohort subjects as indexed Refs. Capture-first only: NO generator, NO list/show (etude-8t4), NO triggers/config (etude-n0t).

