**Manifest field mapping (retro -> runmanifest.Manifest):** per design section 1 \"Manifest fields\":
- RunID = the retro id (refs/etude/retros/<id>); Workflow=\"retro\"; WorkflowVersion=\"retro-v1\"; Created=now UTC.
- Exactly ONE Stage named \"retro\", ProducedBy=\"retro\". GitSHA = HEAD at capture (--git-sha or currentHEAD). Stage.Skill + Producer.Skill required non-empty by Manifest.Validate (skill id/repo/version) -> default skill-id=\"retro\", skill-repo/version from --skill-* flags (default \"manual\"/\"manual\" like capture), Producer.Harness/Model from shared --harness/--model flags.
- The retro BODY is the stage Output ArtifactRef: role=\"retro\", media_type=\"text/markdown; charset=utf-8\", content-addressed via artifactstore.AddContent (read from --file). Body carries the FULL capture-protocol retro schema (scope/trigger/attempt/summary/timeline/failure-modes/root-causes/worked-well/recommendations/follow-up/decision + envelope); Phase B preserves it verbatim as the markdown artifact and does NOT drop fields. No retro-meta JSON sidecar (design marks it Phase B+).
- Cohort SUBJECTS as indexed Manifest.Refs (map[string]string; keys validated [A-Za-z0-9_.-] so the dot in `subject_run.1` is legal, `:`/`@` only ever in VALUES): subject_run.1=<run-id>, subject_run.2=... (one per --subject-run); bead.1=<bead-id> (one per --bead); plus gate.1=<stage@attempt>, bench.1=<id>, eval.1=<id>, supersedes=<retro-id>, decision=<value>, trigger=<value>, scope=<value> as flat keys. The command builds these indexed keys; operators may also pass raw --ref key=value (reuse parseRefs) which merge in.
- Stage.Inputs: empty in this bead. The design's pointer-inputs-into-covered-runs is explicitly optional/Phase B+ (\"Open issues for implementation: pointer inputs ... if not, Phase B records subjects in Refs only and adds pointer inputs in Phase B+\"). So subjects live in Refs ONLY this bead; pointer inputs deferred. Stated here because the design permits this exact reduction.

**CLI surface (etude retro capture <scope>):** grounded in design section 2 Phase B:
- arg <scope>: validated identifier, one of run|phase|gate|cohort|bench|workflow.
- --file (required): path to the retro markdown body (becomes the role=retro output artifact). Mirrors capture-gate's file input; also accept `-` for stdin (design's capture-gate --gate-file precedent: `<path|->`).
- --subject-run <id> (StringArray, repeatable; >=1 required unless scope==workflow) -> validated via runmanifest.IsValidRunID; recorded as subject_run.N. Primary subject (first) feeds RetroIDBase.
- --bead <id> (repeatable) -> bead.N.
- --trigger <name> (default \"manual\"); --decision accepted|deferred|superseded|informational; --supersedes <retro-id>; --gate <stage@attempt> (phase/gate scope); --bench <id> / --eval <id> (bench scope) -> recorded as Refs values.
- shared producer flags from capture: --harness/--harness-version/--model/--skill-id/--skill-repo/--skill-version/--git-sha/--message; plus --ref key=value passthrough.
- behavior: validate scope+flag coherence (e.g. --gate requires phase|gate scope; >=1 subject unless workflow); read --file (or stdin); build Manifest; allocate id via AllocateRetroId(RetroIDBase(scope, primarySubject, now)); write create-only via retro.Writer. Subject runs are validated as ids but NOT required to resolve in this bead (Refs-only; resolving/pinning is Phase B+ pointer-inputs work) — confirm at impl whether to soft-resolve for a friendlier error.
- output: `captured <commit>\nref refs/etude/retros/<id>` (mirror capture).
- errors: --file unreadable; no subjects when scope!=workflow; scope/flag mismatch; id collision after 10 probes (from AllocateRetroId); invalid scope.

