**Risks:**
- Tier-1 four-seat gate (product CLI + new refs/etude/* namespace + storage): the namespace allowlist + validation surface must be exactly parallel to runs/evals — covered by mirroring validateRef/validatePrefix/DeleteRef precisely and adding refstore tests for the new namespace AND continued rejection of unknown namespaces.
- Manifest.Validate requires non-empty per-stage skill id/repo/version + git_sha; the capture command must default these (skill-id=\"retro\", HEAD git_sha) or Validate fails — mirrored from capture.go defaults.
- Artifact-verification reuse: runmanifest.Writer's verifyArtifactFile/referencedArtifactPaths are unexported. Decide at impl: export them from runmanifest (cleaner, single source of truth) vs replicate in internal/retro. Prefer exporting to avoid drift; if it widens the gate surface, replicate with a test asserting parity. Note for reviewers.
- Scope discipline: list/show, generator/seam, triggers, config, retro-meta sidecar, and pointer inputs are all explicitly OUT (etude-8t4 / etude-n0t / Phase B+). Plan records subjects in Refs only.

